      <div class="links">
        <h2>Getting Academic Credit for Learning Outside of Classrooms</h2>
        <p>Prior learning assessment (PLA) is a process that allows individuals to earn academic credit for knowledge and skills they have acquired outside of a traditional classroom setting. Here are
some ways in which prior learning assessment can help individuals earn credit for what they
already know:</p>
        <center><p>〰〰〰</p></center>
        <p>
          PLA acknowledges that individuals can gain
knowledge and skills through a variety of non-traditional learning experiences such as work
experience, military training, volunteering, self-directed study, or hobbies. These experiences
can be evaluated to determine if they meet the learning outcomes of a specific course or
program.
</p> 
        <p>By earning credit for what they already know, individuals can skip courses that cover the material they have already mastered, allowing them to complete their program more quickly and at a lower cost.</p>
       <p> By recognizing their prior learning, learners can see the value of their experiences and feel more confident about their ability to succeed in a college or university setting.
        </p>
        <center><p>〰〰〰</p></center>
      </div>
